---
title: Spicy Cashew Chicken Lo Mein with Dark Meat Chicken, Bell Pepper & Lime
description: Sweet and savory with a touch of heat, this stir-fry is made for busy weeknights but flavorful enough for any day of the week. Succulent chicken cooks with bell pepper, scallion whites, and garlic powder before getting stir-fried with lo mein noodles in a soy-chili sauce. Cashews, scallion greens, and a final squeeze of lime is all that’s needed.
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/673b985ffd3e9058428acbce-5b831da6.jpeg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/673b985ffd3e9058428acbce-en-US.pdf
cuisine: Southeast Asia
nutrition:
  calories: 590 kcal
  fat: 13 g
  saturated fat: 2.5 g
  carbohydrates: 80 g
  sugar: 26 g
  protein: 37 g
  fiber: 3 g
  sodium: 1500 mg
author: Michelle Doll Olson
servings: 2
course: main course
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/spicy-cashew-chicken-lo-mein-673b985ffd3e9058428acbce
time required: 20 minutes
---

Bring a large #pot{} of @water{} and @salt{} to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @green bell pepper{1}. Trim and thinly slice
@scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Quarter @lime{1}.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sweet soy glaze{4%tablespoon}, 
@sweet Thai chili sauce{1%ounce}, @water{1/4%cup}, and as much @sriracha{1%tsp} 
as you like.

Once water is boiling, add @lo mein noodles{4.5%ounce} to pot. Cook, 
stirring occasionally, until al dente, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Drain and set aside until ready to use in Step 4.

Meanwhile, open package of @diced skinless dark meat chicken{10%ounce} and 
drain off any excess liquid.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add
chicken, bell pepper, scallion whites, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Cook, stirring
occasionally, until bell pepper has softened and chicken is cooked through, 
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}; stir to combine.

Stir drained noodles, soy-chili sauce, and juice from one lime wedge 
(two wedges for 4 servings) into pan with chicken and veggies. Cook, 
stirring constantly, until sauce has thickened, ~{1-3%minutes}.

> TIP: If noodles seem dry, add water 1 TBSP at a time until everything is coated
> in sauce.

Divide lo mein between shallow bowls; top with @cashews{1/2%ounce} and 
scallion greens. Serve with any remaining lime wedges on the side.

> Poultry is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.